<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[71532]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[A gran who won't stop]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Montserrat Carulla is coming to Teatre Goya to perform the play, Iaia!, written and directed by her son Roger Peña.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Three generations of Peña-Carullas pay a truly sincere homage to matriarchy in the play &#8220;Iaia!&#8221; which is coming to the Teatre Goya this coming September.</p>
<p>The play tells the story of an old fusspot gran who boycotts her grandson&#8217;s love-life, though it&#8217;s the fact that gran also happens to be Montserrat Carulla that makes the show a must. This is a golden opportunity for enjoying pure Carulla, in a tailor-made role written by her son, Roger Peña, who also plays alongside her grandson, Aleix Peña.</p>
